mistral.reason: Montenegro officially adopted the Deutsche Mark as its de facto currency from 1996, but it did not become its official currency until 1999. The Republic of Montenegro was established in 2006, and the euro had already replaced the Deutsche Mark as the official currency of Montenegro by that time.
